715470f-a.title: Manhattan: 127th Street (East) - Park Avenue
715470f-a.text:
112 East 127th Street, south side, east of Park Avenue, a
20-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 67.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

722403f-b.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 127th Street
722403f-b.text:
(1)
Park Avenue, west side, from 129th to 127th Streets. The houses in
the foreground, 1898-1890 Park Avenue, are three-story frame
structures.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 274.
CREDIT LINE IMPEATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same. Prominent building ahown is the old Harlem Magistrates
Coort.
March 6, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
TNe front of the aforementioned court. Note the bust of President
Lincoln in the triangular facade ornamentation.
March 6, 1936.
L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
